{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-template-js","path":"/headboard/","result":{"pageContext":{"id":"5634bc15-d1d5-56ee-baba-b000462d362a","html":"<h1>headboard</h1>\n<p><em>sometime in 2025</em></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/e83a7/headboard.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.2972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"faux linen headboard\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c72d/headboard.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/a80bd/headboard.jpg 148w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c91a/headboard.jpg 295w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c72d/headboard.jpg 590w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/a8a14/headboard.jpg 885w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/fbd2c/headboard.jpg 1180w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/e83a7/headboard.jpg 3158w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i wanted to get one of those mortise-and-tenon joint bedframes but the cheap one did not come with a headboard. so i made my own!</p>\n<p>i used an ikea desk (don't remember what it is called but about as wide as the frame), and bought upholstery batting, a mattress topper, and a linen-look shower curtain.</p>\n<p>i stapled the mattress topper to the desk top (i also bought a staple gun for this!) and then stapled the batting over it, and then finally the shower curtain.</p>\n<p>this ended up ok, but the shower curtain is not a great texture or match for my sheets (it's about the same color) so i want to change it. i will probably buy real upholstery fabric this time because i can do with just 2 yards i think maybe three.</p>"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}